This paper is about predicting network traffic load at the level of individual flows, which is a problem in the field of computer networking (cs.NI). The approach proposed in the paper involves the use of a kernel-based Kalman filter, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of principal component analysis (PCA) to extract key characteristics of flows, which is a statistical technique (cs.SI). The paper involves the use of signal processing techniques such as the short-time Fourier transform (STFT), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to predict traffic, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
